<h2>The weather in April 2019</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
The monthly temperature for Norway was 3.3&#176;C above the normal (1961-90). It has been the second warmest April ever registered (in a series that goes back to 1900), only April 2011 was warmer. In Svalbard (Spitzbergen) the mean temperature was -3.9&#176;C, which is 8.3&#176;C above the normal. In Svalbard the monthly mean temperature has been above the normal since December 2010, that is 101 months in a row. In France and Spain daily average and maximum temperatures were near average. In Western Russia (Figure 7, left panel) the minimum temperatures were below average which was quite exceptional.
<br><br>
