<h3>Cloudiness and Radiation</h3>
Negative cloud cover anomalies occurred over almost all of Europe (Figure 14), with exceptionally low cloud cover amounts in Western Russia. The sign of the shortwave radiation anomaly (Figure 15) is, as usually, generally opposite to that of the cloud cover anomaly.
<br><br>
